Former President Olusegun Obasanjo on Saturday paid a condolence visit to leader of pan-Yoruba group, Afenifere, Pa Ayo Adebanjo, on the demise of the National Publicity Secretary of the group, Yinka Odumakin. Obasanjo visited the nonagenarian at his Lagos residence to commiserate with him on the death of Odumakin. Odumakin died on Saturday at the Lagos State University Teaching Hospital COVID-19 Isolation Centre. Adebanjo had in a tweet described the death of the Afenifere spokesman as “too heavy to bear”. Odumakin spoke tenaciously for the rights of the Yoruba and the people of the South-West geopolitical zone. The Nation •Yinka Odumakin LAGOS - Mrs Joe Okei-Odumakin, wife of the Afenifere spokesman, Yinka Odumakin, has confirmed the death of her husband from complications arising from of COVID-19. Odumakin, it was learnt, died at the Lagos State University Teaching Hospital isolation centre. His wife, Mrs Joe Okei-Odumakin, confirmed this to The… In "Top Stories" By Bolaji Buhari Lagos -  Former President Olusegun Obasanjo on Saturday met with leaders of the Yoruba socio-cultural group, Afenifere, and other political leaders in the South West on the way forward for Nigeria. The meeting is also about sustaining the unity in Nigeria. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN)… In "Top Stories" •Yinka Odumakin LAGOS - Spokesman of pan-Yoruba socio-political group Afenifere Yinka Odumakin has died of complications from COVID-19. The activist had been on ventilator at a treatment centre in Lagos, Qed.ng learned. Qed.ng was informed that he had serious underlining conditions including diabetes, lung-related issues and a mild stroke first… In "Top Stories"